<Document>
<name>Grossglockner High Alpine Road</name>
<description><![CDATA[<h2>Grossglockner High Alpine Road</h2><p><i>Salzburg / Carinthia, Austria · Grossglockner-Hochalpenstrasse, Zell am See to Heiligenblut</i></p><p><b>36 hairpins, summit at 2,504 m, Austria's highest road and longest glacier on display.</b></p><table style='font-family:sans-serif'><tr><td><b>Approx. length:</b></td><td>44 km (27 mi)</td></tr><tr><td><b>Drive time:</b></td><td>3–4 hrs (toll road, plan for stops)</td></tr><tr><td><b>Best season:</b></td><td>Early May–late October (gates locked at night and off-season)</td></tr><tr><td><b>Watch out for:</b></td><td>Toll cost (high), weather (snow possible in summer), motorcyclists, marmots crossing road</td></tr><tr><td><b>Track points:</b></td><td>108</td></tr></table><hr><p>Built 1930–35 by 4,000 workers — partly a Depression-era make-work project, partly a deliberate national symbol of Austrian engineering between the wars. 48 km of paved alpine theatre with 36 numbered hairpins, summit at Hochtor 2,504 m. The Pasterze, Austria's longest glacier, is the showstopper — though it's retreating fast (down to 8 km from 14 km in 1850, with markers along the access road showing the rate). Bring a jacket; even July mornings are cold up top. Spur drives to Edelweißspitze (highest road point at 2,571 m) and Kaiser-Franz-Josefs-Höhe (face-on to the Großglockner massif and the glacier) are mandatory.</p><h3>Scenic points marked on this route:</h3><ul><li><b>Edelweißspitze</b> — Highest point of the road at 2,571 m. 360° panorama of more than 30 alpine peaks above 3,000 m. Cobblestone parking lot — the original 1935 surface.</li><li><b>Fuscher Törl</b> — Memorial chapel honoring road-construction workers killed during the build. Alpine basin with marmot colonies.</li><li><b>Hochtor tunnel</b> — Summit of the route at 2,504 m, in a 311 m road tunnel under the watershed. Italian/Roman-era trade objects have been excavated nearby — this was the route Roman traders used.</li><li><b>Kaiser-Franz-Josefs-Höhe</b> — Face-on view of the Pasterze (Austria's longest glacier, 8 km) and the Großglockner (Austria's highest peak, 3,798 m). Visitor centre with glacier-retreat exhibition.</li><li><b>Heiligenblut church</b> — Late-Gothic pilgrimage church (1483) said to hold a vial of Christ's blood. Photographed against the Großglockner; Austria's most painted view.</li></ul><hr><p><i>Track geometry is interpolated between named waypoints — use a routing service to snap to actual road for navigation. Waypoints, scenic POIs, and notes are reliable.</i></p>]]></description>
